This paper deals with the problem of Bayesian linear regression with differential privacy, which involves machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes noise-aware methods for inference, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
